API: https://docs.atlassian.com/confluence/REST/latest/#content-getContent

Our organization is currently developing a plugin which allows you to edit the source for a confluence page. Currently when you make a call to getContent in the connect rest API for a page with an image, you get back something that looks like this:

{code:javascript}
{
...
    "body": {
        "view": {
            "value": "<img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">",
            "representation": "storage",
            "_expandable": {
                "content": "/rest/api/content/1234"
            }
        }
    },
...
}
{code}

The rest API is saying that the format being returned is storage format, but that is incorrect because in XHTML you must close out all <img> tags. This means that what is actually being returned is *view format*, and not actually storage format.

We discovered this when we tried to save the content of a page with an image in it. If you get the content of a page with an image in it, you won't be able to save the exact same content because it is not valid XHTML.

Here are the two underlying issues:
* Does the API need to be saying that it is returning view format instead of storage?
* How can we control what format we get from getContent (i.e. storage versus view).

